Program: bookstore() 
create and test bookstore()
bookstore() takes 2 string arguments: book & price 
bookstore returns a string in sentence form 
bookstore() should call title_it_rtn() with book parameter 
gather input for book_entry and price_entry to use in calling bookstore() 
print the return value of bookstore()
example of output:Title: The Adventures Of Sherlock Holmes, costs $12.99
# [ ] create, call and test bookstore() function 
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Ans

def title_it_rtn(book):
    book = book.Title()
    return book
    
def bookstore(book,price) :
   output = "Title: " + title_it_rtn(book) + ", cost $" + price
   return output
            
book_entry = input("Name of the book: ")
book_price = input("Price of the book: ")
            
print(bookstore(book_entry,book_price))


output :
Name of the book: the adevntures of shelock homes                                                                                                                                  
Price of the book: 12.99                                                                                                                                                           
Title: The Adevntures Of Shelock Homes, cost $12.9

